Test Buddy master takeover - cluster survives node failure with RF=2
––– comment –––
Start 3-node cluster
––– input –––
export INSTANCE=1
––– output –––
––– block: ../../base/replication/start-searchd-precach –––
––– input –––
export INSTANCE=2
––– output –––
––– block: ../../base/replication/start-searchd-precach –––
––– input –––
export INSTANCE=3
––– output –––
––– block: ../../base/replication/start-searchd-precach –––
––– input –––
export CLUSTER_NAME=c TABLE_NAME=t
––– output –––
––– block: ../../base/replication/create-cluster –––
––– block: ../../base/replication/join-cluster-on-all-nodes –––
––– comment –––
Create table with RF=2 (each shard has 2 copies for HA) - auto-sharding creates cluster c
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P1306 -e "CREATE TABLE ${CLUSTER_NAME}:${TABLE_NAME} (id bigint, value string) shards='2' rf='2'"; echo $?
––– output –––
0
––– input –––
show_shards 1306 "$TABLE_NAME"
––– output –––
system.t_s0: 127.0.0.1:1312 127.0.0.1:3312
system.t_s1: 127.0.0.1:1312 127.0.0.1:2312
––– comment –––
Kill master node (node 1) - Buddy will detect and handle failover
––– input –––
export INSTANCE=1; stdbuf -oL searchd --stopwait -c test/clt-tests/base/searchd-with-flexible-ports.conf > /dev/null; echo "Node 1 killed"
––– output –––
Node 1 killed
––– comment –––
Wait to be sure port is gone
––– input –––
timeout 30 bash -c 'while lsof -i :${INSTANCE}306 &>/dev/null; do sleep 1; done'
––– output –––
––– comment –––
If grep fails due to missing string or timeout, return non-zero
––– input –––
timeout 10 grep -qm1 'becoming master' <(tail -n 1000 -f /var/log/manticore-{2,3}/searchd.log); echo $?
––– output –––
0
––– comment –––
Verify remaining 2 nodes are still synced (RF=2 maintained)
––– input –––
for i in 2 3; do check_cluster_status ${i}306 "$CLUSTER_NAME"; done | uniq
––– output –––
OK
––– comment –––
Verify that shards was rebalanced
––– input –––
show_shards 2306 "$TABLE_NAME"
––– output –––
system.t_s0: 127.0.0.1:2312 127.0.0.1:3312
system.t_s1: 127.0.0.1:2312 127.0.0.1:3312
––– comment –––
Restart killed node (node 1)
––– input –––
export INSTANCE=1
––– output –––
––– block: ../../base/replication/start-searchd-precach –––
––– comment –––
Give some time for node to rejoin and resync
––– input –––
sleep 2
––– output –––
––– comment –––
Check that cluster is synced
––– input –––
for i in 1 2 3; do check_cluster_status ${i}306 "$CLUSTER_NAME"; done | uniq
––– output –––
OK
––– comment –––
At this point we should not rebalance old table on new node addition
––– input –––
show_shards 2306 "$TABLE_NAME"
––– output –––
system.t_s0: 127.0.0.1:2312 127.0.0.1:3312
system.t_s1: 127.0.0.1:2312 127.0.0.1:3312

